going_detailed: Straight course - GOOD TO YIELDING changing to YIELDING after Race 1 (1.45); Round course - YIELDING

runners.name: Bad Boy Rizz
runners.comment: Rated 74 after four maiden runs at 5f-6f, beaten 4.75l latest, place claims
runners.spotlight: Rated 74 after four runs in maidens at 5f-6f; beaten 4.75l when third of 12 at Down Royal (5f, good) on latest; more needed to win but he has place claims.

runners.name: Battleforsupremacy
runners.comment: Looks one for handicaps based on the evidence of his first two runs
runners.spotlight: Rates an unlikely winner on the back of sound defeats at Down Royal and Navan; may do better when sent handicapping.

runners.name: Ennoble
runners.comment: Not disgraced in two 6f Curragh maidens, needs more dropped back to 5f
runners.spotlight: Not disgraced in first two starts in 6f Curragh maidens on good ground; needs to find more on first start at 5f.

runners.name: Sceitimini
runners.comment: Hard to fancy after heavy debut defeat, may need more time
runners.spotlight: Impossible to fancy after 26l defeat on debut at Killarney in July; may need more time.

runners.name: Cactus
runners.comment: Rated 77 after six starts, latest start too bad to be true but not one for maximum trust
runners.spotlight: By the late Wootton Bassett and rated 77 after six starts; beaten in handicaps in two of last three starts; latest effort too bad to be true and capable of better but doesn't look one for maximum trust.

runners.name: Realistic Dream
runners.comment: 33-1 and beaten 12.5l on debut on heavy (7f), Tornado Kiss looks yard's main hope
runners.spotlight: Beaten 12.5l on debut at Killarney (7f, heavy) when 33-1; drops back in trip on different ground now; Tornado Kiss looks yard's main hope.

runners.name: Rumba Club
runners.comment: Pleasing third on debut at Naas, place chance if handling this better ground
runners.spotlight: Coulsty filly made a very pleasing start when a 5.25l third off 11 at Naas (5f, soft) 12 days ago when lugging left under pressure; place claims if building on that and handling better ground.

runners.name: Tornado Kiss
runners.comment: Narrow defeats first two starts at Naas at 5f-6f on varying ground, will be tough to beat
runners.spotlight: Acclamation filly beaten a neck on debut at Naas (5f, good, ran green) in July and 0.5l back there over 6f (yld-sft) on latest when keen early; a repeat of either of those runs should be enough to take this; the one to beat.

quotes.quote: She went too free in Naas so we dropped Tornado Kiss back to 5f. She's lazy at home and doesn't show it, I think she's a 5f filly. We're thinking of going for the Cornwallis at Newmarket in a fortnight, or maybe we'll let her off, she's a big, raw filly - Andy Slattery, trainer, speaking to Racing TV

race_name: Irish Stallion Farms EBF Nursery Handicap
going_detailed: Straight course - GOOD TO YIELDING changing to YIELDING after Race 1 (1.45); Round course - YIELDING

runners.name: Allsortz
runners.comment: Good efforts in a couple of maidens, gelded, opening mark doesn't look generous
runners.spotlight: Best maiden effort a 1.5l fourth at Fairyhouse (6f, gd-yld); caught the eye when a 4.75l seventh at Leopardstown last time; has been gelded and not discounted in first nursery but handicapper hasn't taken any chances with his opening mark.

runners.name: Joyful Tidings
runners.breeder: Mr M Dunphy & Mr E Cantillon
runners.comment: Maiden winner, shade keen in valuable sales race latest, can go well if settles better
runners.spotlight: Beat a decent sort when winning a 5f Tipperary maiden (yielding) on debut in April; only run since a respectable 5l fifth in valuable sales race at the Curragh (6.5f, yielding); raced a shade keenly that day; can go well if settling better.

runners.name: Nakamura
runners.comment: Won decisively off 9lb lower at Navan, blinkers retained, ground fine, chance
runners.spotlight: Off the mark at the third attempt in handicaps in decisive fashion at Navan last month (6f, yielding, Glamazon fourth); blinkers worn that day are retained; raised 9lb but he looks progressive and he's got form on good ground; chance.

runners.name: Raphello
runners.breeder: Newtown Stud And T J Pabst
runners.comment: Run well in defeat in three of last four starts, needs more to get head in front
runners.spotlight: Narrow defeat in a Sligo maiden in early August followed by a good third on nursery debut at the Curragh; another decent effort off this mark at Fairyhouse on latest; needs to find a bit more to get his head in front.

runners.name: Soy El Fuego
runners.comment: Beaten fav' last two maidens, opening mark look fair, could go well on h'cap debut
runners.spotlight: Handicap debutant was a beaten favourite in his last two maidens at Bellewstown (5f, good) and over this C&D (soft); opening mark looks fair and he could go well.

runners.name: Bay Of Supremacy
runners.owner: Kildare Racing Syndicate & Kilmichael Racing Syndicate
runners.comment: Up 6lb for handicap debut win at Naas, Ben Coen prefers the chances of Nakamura
runners.spotlight: Second runner for yard; left modest maiden form behind to win on nursery debut at Naas 12 days ago (6f, soft) in first-time blinkers (retained); 6lb rise negated by rider's claim but Ben Coen prefers Nakamura.

quotes.quote: The blinkers were a big help. Bay Of Supremacy worked in them the other day and Ben said he gets through the ground really well. There is a 5f race next week at Down Royal and we'll probably let him go again. We'll keep him busy while the ground is soft - Johnny Murtagh, trainer.

runners.name: Fleur De Rose
runners.comment: Promise in maidens, stayed on well over 5f here latest, interesting on h'cap debut
runners.spotlight: Definite promise in maidens, including when beaten 2l over 5f here on latest; shaped like 6f would suit and her opening mark looks more than fair; could be a big player.

runners.name: Ardadslosttheplot
runners.breeder: Shaikh Khalid Bin Ali Al Khalifa
runners.comment: Good run on second start at Down Royal (7f), worth a market check on nursery debut
runners.spotlight: Best of three maiden runs came second time up over 7f at Down Royal (good), a 1.75l third at 80-1; easy ground may not have suited on latest; not sure 6f will suit on nursery debut but worth a market check nonetheless.

runners.name: Glamazon
runners.comment: Behind Nakamura and Joyful Tidings last twice, better off at weights but more needed
runners.spotlight: Promise in maidens and went close on handicap debut at Sligo off 68; 5.75l behind Nakamura at Navan on penultimate and behind Joyful Tidings in valuable sales race at the Curragh latest; better off at weights but more needed to turn tables.

runners.name: Sup Of Red
runners.comment: 1.5l behind Bay Of Supremacy latest, has form at 6f, yard's runners often go well here
runners.spotlight: Finished 1.5l behind Bay Of Supremacy off this mark at Naas last time out (5f, soft); ran well over this trip on good ground in a Navan maiden previously; yard's runners often go well here and she is not discounted.

runners.name: Bullet Bourbon
runners.breeder: D Daly, G Shevlin & D Battersby
runners.owner: David Daly & Gerard Shevlin & D Battersby
runners.comment: Yard won this last year, ran on nicely after slow start on h'cap bow, may outrun odds
runners.spotlight: Represents last year's winning trainer; minor maiden promise and ran on nicely enough after being awkward at the start on handicap debut at Fairyhouse (6f, yielding); dropped 2lb and could outrun likely odds.

runners.name: Cisterna
runners.comment: Not far behind a couple of these latest, 1lb wrong, needs to find improvement to figure
runners.spotlight: Not beaten that far when eighth behind Bay Of Supremacy and Sup Of Red at Naas (5f, soft) off 60; however, he's 1lb wrong here and he needs to find improvement to figure.

runners.name: Disco Version
runners.comment: Ordinary maiden efforts, 14lb out of the handicap, hard to make a case for on form
runners.spotlight: Ordinary form in maidens at 5f-6f; rated 47 so is 14lb out of the handicap here; difficult to make a case for on form.

race_name: Irish Stallion Farms EBF Fillies Handicap
going_detailed: Straight course - GOOD TO YIELDING changing to YIELDING after Race 1 (1.45); Round course - YIELDING

runners.name: Convo
runners.comment: No joy since debut win, heavy defeat at Espom when last seen, watch on stable debut
runners.spotlight: Won on debut for Amy Murphy in France last year before a listed second at Chantilly; has regressed since and left Lemos De Souza after a heavy defeat in an Epsom handicap; best watched on first run for Jack Davison.

runners.name: Likedbymike
runners.owner: Mrs Michael J Byrne & Jerry P Murphy
runners.comment: Course maiden winner (5f), lost way since promising reappearance run, cheekpieces tried
runners.spotlight: Impressive 5f maiden (gd-yld) winner here on third start last year; solid effort on seasonal reappearance back here in a 5f rated race (1.75l behind the now 99 rated Town And Country); below that level since and now cheekpieces reached for; needs to revive.

runners.name: Staysound Susie
runners.comment: Won this after a break last year off 2lb higher, likely primed for this, big chance
runners.spotlight: Returned from a two month break to win this race off 76 last year; is back for a repeat bid off 2lb lower after a 109 day break; 7f was too far here on latest and she is likely to have been primed for this; big chance on ground that will suit.

runners.name: Amicitia
runners.comment: Off the mark over 5f at Navan, up 11lb in deeper race but could be more to come
runners.spotlight: Promise in maidens at 7f-6f and on handicap debut at the Curragh (6f, gd-yld); drop to 5f did the trick at Navan 24 days ago where she won with authority off 64; up 11lb and this is a deeper race but could be more to come from this unexposed 3yo.

runners.name: Aurora Nova
runners.comment: Won three this season, ran poorly over C&D in July, seems best on turning tracks
runners.spotlight: Won three at 5f this season, two of those victories coming at Bellewstown; narrowly denied back there on penultimate off 75 and 2lb lower now; ran poorly over this C&D in July and she is more effective on turning tracks.

runners.name: Amemri
runners.comment: Completed five-timer off 4lb lower in June, beaten twice since, needs to rebound
runners.spotlight: Nine-time winner, six on the AW and three on turf; completed a five-timer when winning at Limerick (1m, good) in June off 68; 4lb higher here and needs to rebound from below par efforts at Killarney and Leopardstown.

quotes.quote: Amemri was part of the syndicate but she just wasn't selling for enough so I bought her as a present for my wife. She's been remarkable. We thought she might win a couple but that's five in a row now and six since we bought her, while she won three for the syndicate - David Marnane, trainer.
Amemri is a good and tough mare. I was happy all the way and I probably got there soon enough turning in, but it worked out grand - Luke McAteer, rider.

runners.name: White Clover
runners.owner: James V Purcell & Crampscastle Bloodstock Ltd
runners.comment: Won off 4lb lower in June, went close off this mark at Naas, has run well over C&D
runners.spotlight: Won at Listowel (6.5f, gd-yld) in June off 68; no impact off revised mark next three starts but then went close at Naas (7f, gd-yld) off 72; no apparent excuses when midfield at Fairyhouse latest; not easy to predict but has run well over C&D.

quotes.quote: White Clover will probably run again, we will see what the handicapper does but the intention was to run her again. I took a little punt and put her in that Mallow handicap in three weeks and if she got in at the bottom of the weight she could have a little squeak over seven furlongs. We were hoping we would win today to get her into it. She has been threatening to be a good filly for a good few years now so we will find out shortly if she is or not - Joseph Murphy, trainer.

runners.name: Bundle Of Interest
runners.comment: Won over 6f at Navan in July, hasn't really threatened since, this may be too sharp a test
runners.spotlight: Scored off 69 at Navan in July (6f, good); not disgraced off revised mark the last twice but hasn't really threatened to win; stayed on over 7f at Gowran latest; this may be too sharp a test.

runners.name: Pickersgill
runners.comment: Struggled in two handicaps since maiden win in March, off since May, others appeal more
runners.spotlight: Won a Curragh maiden (6f, soft) on seasonal reappearance in March; soundly beaten in two handicaps subsequently; dropped 8lb for latest run in May; can go well fresh but others make more appeal.

quotes.race: Visit The Irish National Stud & Gardens Maiden
quotes.quote: Pickersgill is a bit opinionated in the parade ring and Robbie said she wasn't doing a tap in front. She got spooked 200 metres from the line at the yellow marker and then she just picked up and went again. She's better than what she showed there as if there is something to bring her further into the race, it would suit her. She had them off the bridle quite early on. She's going the right way and is improving. I don't think soft ground is a must for her but a lot of Starspangledbanners do enjoy a cut - Sheila Lavery, trainer.

runners.name: Winters Breath
runners.breeder: Al Shira'Aa Farms S A R L
runners.comment: Blew the start when 5l behind Amicitia on handicap bow, 11lb swing, could go well
runners.spotlight: Second runner for yard; eyecatcher when a 5l fifth on handicap debut at Navan (5f, good) behind Amicitia after badly missing the break; 11lb better off with that rival now and McMonagle booked; could go well if getting away on level terms.

runners.name: Shoney
runners.comment: Maiden winner, first two starts for this yard well below that level, hard to fancy
runners.spotlight: Maiden winner for Willie McCreery at Tipperary in May (5f, yld-sft); first two starts for current yard well below that level; mark sliding but hard to fancy on the back of those efforts.

quotes.race: It's A Long Way To Being 50 Shane Anderson Maiden
quotes.quote: She ran well at Sligo and thought Shoney come on for it and she did, she was good. She jumped well from the gates and travelled and I was able to tack across to the middle of the track. When I gave her a squeeze, everything behind me when silent and I had gone clear. She's not big but she's hardy. She's a good mover, I think she'll go on any ground - Billy Lee, jockey, speaking to Racing TV

runners.name: Kwa Herini
runners.comment: 0-10, has run well in defeat, not beaten far latest off this mark, cheekpieces go on
runners.spotlight: 0-10 but has often run well in defeat; good second at the Curragh (6.5f, good) in June off 2lb higher; not beaten far off this mark at Fairyhouse (6f, yielding latest); new cheekpieces need to eke out a bit more.

going_detailed: Straight course - GOOD TO YIELDING changing to YIELDING after Race 1 (1.45); Round course - YIELDING

runners.name: Im Spartacus
runners.comment: Third at Ayr last month and wasn't far away after a troubled run on the AW last week
runners.spotlight: Third over 6f at Ayr last month and wasn't far away after a troubled run on the AW last week; considered.

runners.name: Devils Angel

prev_owners.owner: One In A Million Syndicate/B Sheerin/G O'Brien/K Coleman

runners.comment: Nine-time winner but beaten 7l and 10l since changing trainers, latterly at Laytown
runners.spotlight: Nine-time winner but beaten 7l and 10l since changing trainers, latterly at Laytown when backed into favouritism for a claimer.

quotes.race: Sky Bet Sunday Series Sprint Handicap
quotes.quote: We couldn't believe the price he was for a horse that won two starts ago. I know Devil's Angel is a bit hit and miss because of his minor issue with the stalls, but he was still a huge price. He loves Sandown (won both starts there) and we'll look at a choice of races at the Saturday and Sunday meeting there in two weeks' time - Jedd O'Keeffe, trainer.

quotes.race: Play 4 To Score At Betway Handicap
quotes.quote: It was a good bit of placing. There wasn't much pace on paper so I sat close and Devil's Angel gave me an easy ride. It was the right track to experiment going five and maybe he will stay at that trip now - Oisin Murphy, jockey.

quotes.race: Thank You Dr Jerry Hill Handicap (Jockey Club Grassroots Sprint Series Qualifier)
quotes.quote: Callum Shepherd has given Devil's Angel a lovely ride as he lugs left when he hits the front. He's the right colour, so the plan is come back for the grey horse handicap next month - Chris Vallice, syndicate spokesman.

runners.name: Step Back In Time
runners.comment: Only 3-34 but ran a good race in defeat at Navan (5f) and returning to 6f is no hardship
runners.spotlight: Only 3-34 but ran a good race in defeat at Navan (5f) and returning to 6f is no hardship; claims.

quotes.quote: Step Back In Time got away with it today over the stiff five, she probably wants six. She ground it out really well. She has not been running badly and came out of the Cork race very well - Chris Timmons, trainer.

runners.name: Jazzy Dancer
runners.comment: Returns to turf after three AW runs this year, the latest in February; bit risky
runners.spotlight: Returns to turf after three AW runs this year and the first two were competitive (behind I'm Spartacus on second occasion); has been off since February, though.

quotes.race: Gannon Office Solutions Supporting Kildare Chamber Handicap
quotes.quote: Jazzy Dancer was a horse we have been patient with and he looks like a horse that can go in again. Hopefully the handicapper won't be too hard on him - Mick Martin, assistant trainer.

runners.name: Ukiyo
runners.comment: 0-4 in maidens for previous yard and fairly well held in two sprint handicaps for this one
runners.spotlight: 0-4 in maidens for previous yard and fairly well held in two sprint handicaps for this one.

runners.name: Reponse Finale
runners.comment: No wins in 12 and handicap mark is spiralling for a reason; others preferred
runners.spotlight: No wins in 12 and handicap mark is spiralling for a reason; others preferred.

runners.name: American In Paris
runners.comment: Ahead of Devil's Angel when third in a Laytown claimer but that was a poor race
runners.spotlight: Naas winner over 6f in July when first tried in this headgear combination; ahead of Devil's Angel when third in a Laytown claimer but that was a poor race.

stable_tour.quote: She was extraordinarily green on her debut at Bath when running one of the most eyecatching races of the season. She was slowly away and last at halfway before really picking up in the last quarter-mile. To my eye she made up fully 12 lengths to go down by a short head. If ever the cliché “a winner without a penalty” applied to a horse, it's her. You should watch the video and you won't believe the ground she made up. If she learned anything at Bath her turn will come very soon. 06-07-22

runners.name: Romantic War
runners.comment: Had plenty of chances now and no signs of late to suggest he'll be winning soon
runners.spotlight: Had plenty of chances now and no signs of late to suggest he'll be winning soon.

runners.name: Shoebox King
runners.comment: Modest strike-rate and comfortably beaten in two runs after a break; now back from another
runners.spotlight: Modest strike-rate and comfortably beaten in two runs after a break; now back from another with blinkers back on.

quotes.quote: It's hard in Ireland in those lower grades as there are a lot of horses with not much between them. I think he's genuine enough. We'll probably put Shoebox King in the August Sale now. I think he's done his job here and he'd be a good horse for England - Kevin Coleman, trainer.

runners.name: Star Sailor
runners.comment: Soft ground perhaps not ideal after an absence but his mark has bottomed out
runners.spotlight: Runner-up in a handicap last year and soft ground perhaps not ideal when well beaten after more than a year off; mark has bottomed out.

runners.name: Sovereign Banter
runners.comment: 0-13 but was fourth of 21 here on stable debut and seemed stretched by the 7f on soft
runners.spotlight: 0-13 but was fourth of 21 here on stable debut and seemed stretched by the 7f on soft ground; could go well with more new headgear tried.

going_detailed: Straight course - GOOD TO YIELDING changing to YIELDING after Race 1 (1.45); Round course - YIELDING

runners.name: Almeiyda
runners.breeder: His Highness The Aga Khan's Studs S C
runners.owner: Exors Of The Late H H Aga Khan
runners.comment: Newcomer representing same connections who won this in 2023 with a top-class filly
runners.spotlight: First foal out of a 1m2f winner (RPR 93), out of 1m4f Listed winning half-sister to 1m6f/2m4f Group 1 winner Alandi; same connections won this two years ago with their subsequent Oaks winner Ezeliya (did have the benefit of a run).

runners.name: Ballaghkeen
runners.comment: Beaten in the region of 10l in two 1m maidens and already looks one for handicaps
runners.spotlight: Beaten in the region of 10l in two 1m maidens and already looks one for handicaps.

runners.name: Bloom
runners.owner: Mrs John Magnier & Michael Tabor & Derrick Smith
runners.comment: 15-2 at Leopardstown and was beaten under 5l; can improve on that
runners.spotlight: Wootton Bassett filly out of a Listed winner by Galileo; 15-2 at Leopardstown and was beaten under 5l; can improve on that and she's raised in trip.

quotes.quote: I always thought I had it covered, just had to get Bloom organised as she's a big filly and very laidback but she knuckled down well. I think her last furlong was her best and she hit the line strong. - Jack Cleary, jockey, speaking to Racing TV

runners.name: Celestially
runners.comment: Fifth foal; dam placed 6f/7f (RPR 68), closely related to 7f-2m winner Royal Reserve
runners.spotlight: Fifth foal; dam placed 6f/7f (RPR 68), closely related to 7f-2m winner Royal Reserve; one of three runners for the yard.

runners.name: Chablis Rock
runners.comment: Half-sister to high-class stayer Coltrane and may need further in time
runners.spotlight: Half-sister to high-class stayer Coltrane, Warda Jamila (1m/1m2f; 93) and Zonisty (AW bumper); dam unraced sister to 1m6f/2m Flat and smart 2m-2m4f hurdle winner Tigris River; may need further but needs checking in the betting; trainer runs two.

runners.name: Coolangatta
runners.comment: Finished 13th of the 15 runners on good ground at Naas (7f) and readily opposed here
runners.spotlight: Finished 13th of the 15 runners on good ground at Naas (7f) and readily opposed here.

runners.name: I Hope You Dance
runners.breeder: Framont Limited & Guy Pariente Holding Sprl
runners.comment: 37,000gns yearling; fifth foal; closely related to French 6f/6.7f winner Expertise
runners.spotlight: 37,000gns yearling; fifth foal; closely related to French 6f/6.7f winner Expertise, half-sister to winners Atome (French 7f) and Thaleem (KSA 6f 2yo); unraced dam out of 7f/1m Listed winning half-sister to 6.5f Group 1 winner Polydream; the betting can guide.

runners.name: Ifweonlyhavelove
runners.breeder: Haras Des Evees, M Daniel Cherdo & Mme Claudie Cherdo
runners.comment: Not a bad debut when fifth of nine at Punchestown but doesn't appeal as a likely winner
runners.spotlight: It wasn't a bad debut when fifth of nine at Punchestown but doesn't appeal as a likely winner of this.

runners.name: Itsyouitsyouitsyou
runners.comment: Half-sister to 1m Flat (RPR 83)/2m hurdle winner Action Plan; dam unraced
runners.spotlight: Half-sister to 1m Flat (RPR 83)/2m hurdle winner Action Plan; dam unraced half-sister to 7f winner Mulhimatty; likely best watched.

runners.name: Jojos Legacy
runners.comment: Second run better than the first but will need another jolt of improvement
runners.spotlight: Behind Ridersinthesky on her debut here and was 6l off the winner when third at Gowran (ahead of Rayzera); will need a further jolt of improvement to be winning this.

runners.name: Keepsgettingbetter
runners.owner: Mrs Richard Henry & Mrs John Magnier
runners.comment: Sister to French 1m1f AW 2yo winner Chauncey Gardiner; dam 8.5f/1m1f winner
runners.spotlight: Second foal; sister to French 1m1f AW 2yo winner Chauncey Gardiner; dam 8.5f/1m1f winner (German Listed; RPR 107); the market may file her yard's runners into some pecking order.

runners.name: Lamberella
runners.comment: 35,000euros yearling; third foal; half-sister to winner Zoffandia (1m AW; RPR 84)
runners.spotlight: 35,000euros yearling; third foal; half-sister to winners Zoffandia (1m AW; RPR 84) and Donnia (Polish 5f 2yo/7f); dam French 8.5f/9.5f winner; one of two newcomers for her yard.

runners.name: Rayzera
runners.breeder: His Highness The Aga Khan's Studs S C
runners.owner: Exors Of The Late H H Aga Khan
runners.comment: Nicely-bred filly who was beaten 9l on debut at Gowran four weeks ago (7f)
runners.spotlight: Nicely-bred filly who was beaten 9l on debut at Gowran four weeks ago (7f); needs more here but the extra yardage can help.

runners.name: Ridersinthesky
runners.comment: Commendable show for a maiden to make the frame in a Group 3 last time
runners.spotlight: Third at the Curragh and here (7f both times) before again making the frame in a Group 3 back at the Curragh (1m, good), which was a commendable show for a maiden; leading claims.

runners.name: River Ara
runners.owner: Westerberg, Mrs J Magnier, M Tabor, D Smith
runners.comment: Both runs over 7f, last time proving no match for a 3l winner at this track
runners.spotlight: St Mark's Basilica filly cost 300,000gns as a yearling; both runs over 7f, last time proving no match for a 3l winner at this track; dam stayed well so this step up to 1m can only help.

runners.name: Yousaynothingatall
runners.comment: Second foal; sister to 1m (2yo) and 1m2f (Group 3) winner Wemighttakedlongway (RPR 112)
runners.spotlight: Second foal; sister to 1m (2yo) and 1m2f (Group 3) winner Wemighttakedlongway (RPR 112); dam unraced sister to Group-placed 1m winner Emphatic Answer; trainer also runs fellow newcomer Chablis Rock.

race_name: Irish Stallion Farms EBF Navigation Stakes (Listed Race)
going_detailed: Straight course - GOOD TO YIELDING changing to YIELDING after Race 1 (1.45); Round course - YIELDING

runners.name: Cadogan
runners.owner: N C Williams & Mrs Paul Shanahan & Mrs M V Magnier

prev_owners.owner: LLoyd J Williams & Mrs Paul Shanahan & Mrs M V Magnier

runners.comment: Will need to be better than his mark of 93 to land this but that's feasible
runners.spotlight: Pushed the classy Henri Matisse close on debut at the Curragh (6f) last year and returned from a gelding operation to win his maiden at Leopardstown (1m1f, good); will need to be better than his mark of 93 to land this but that's feasible.

runners.name: Eastwatch
runners.comment: Dual winner but has been comfortably beaten in his two previous cracks at Listed races
runners.spotlight: Dual winner but has been comfortably beaten in his two previous cracks at Listed races, over 1m1f and 1m6f; others preferred.

quotes.quote: Look at the size of Eastwatch. I think the sky is the limit for him when he gets to four years old. He was idling the whole way up the straight and nearly got himself beat looking around the place. He's a big baby. We ran him at Leopardstown. We jumped him off in behind. We were happy with that run but disappointed with the way we rode him. I think he could even be a Melbourne Cup horse. I'd love to put him away now for another while and wait until September or October - Andrew Slattery, trainer.

runners.name: Isambard Brunel
runners.owner: Derrick Smith & Mrs John Magnier & Michael Tabor
runners.comment: Off since tailed off in the Listed Dee Stakes at Chester's May meeting; now blinkered
runners.spotlight: Convincing winner of a Navan 1m maiden last October; confined to one run in the meantime when tailed off in the Listed Dee Stakes at Chester's May meeting (first-time tongue-tie); now has some questions to answer and blinkers are called for.

quotes.race: Navan Racecourse Welcomes Our Local Community Maiden
quotes.quote: The trip would be bang up his street and he'd have the class to go into it [Futurity Trophy]. It'll just be down to ground. Isambard Brunel can go with ease in the ground but, to go into a race like that there, he would prefer better ground. He's a typical Justify. He has plenty of size and strength and is a very good mover. Either way, he's a horse with plenty to look forward to for next year - Chris Armstrong, assistant trainer.

stable_tour.quote: He won his maiden at Navan well last season and is back in full work and in good form, nearly ready to start. There's a winners' race at Cork later this month and, all being well, he's a possible for that. 07-04-25

runners.name: Purview
runners.comment: A beaten favourite the last twice but in good races and he retains significant potential
runners.spotlight: Twice a beaten favourite (Group 3/Listed) since chasing home Delacroix in Leopardstown's Derby Trial (1m2f, good) back in May and no question that France last time was a backward step; however, he remains a colt of considerable potential.

runners.name: Reyenzi
runners.owner: Exors Of The Late H H Aga Khan
runners.comment: Demoted from first in a Group 3; latest run at that level didn't really go to plan
runners.spotlight: Lost a Group 3 in the stewards room earlier this year; odds-on when beaten in a handicap at Naas (1m2f, good) and never got involved from off the pace when tried hooded in a Group 3 on Irish Champions Weekend at Leopardstown (1m4f); might yet be capable of better.

stable_tour.quote: I was very happy with his run last time. I was disappointed to lose it in the stewards' room but he deserves his chance now. The Hampton Court Stakes trip will suit him.  13-06-25

runners.name: Tangapour
runners.breeder: His Highness The Aga Khan's Studs S C
runners.owner: Exors Of The Late H H Aga Khan
runners.comment: Balance of form suggests his front-running second in a Group 3 is grossly flattering
runners.spotlight: Rated only 80 when outrunning odds of 300-1 as a pacemaker for his successful stablemate Zahrann in a Group 3 at the Curragh last time; unwise to take that form at face value given the balance of his achievements and Ben Coen prefers Reyenzi.

runners.name: Iowa City
runners.comment: Receiving weight off an older horse who had a mark of 89 when winning at Galway
runners.spotlight: Joined this yard for 210,000euros after showing useful form in nine French races; did well to get up in the nick of time in a rated race at Galway but she was receiving weight off an older horse who had a mark of 89; this race demands improvement.

runners.name: Sharpen
runners.owner: Dj Stable Llc, Medallion, Weston, Hoffman
runners.comment: Only her fourth race when second in a 1m4f Listed race; this does look stronger, though
runners.spotlight: 1m2f maiden winner who confirmed herself progressive when on only her fourth start ran close in a 1m4f Listed race at Gowran (good) two months ago; this is stronger but shouldn't be underestimated with the promise of more to come.

quotes.race: Glenroyal Hotel And Shoda Cafe Irish EBF Fillies Maiden
quotes.quote: Sharpen is a very nice filly. She got terrible ground on her debut at Naas but we have given her a bit of time since then. She stayed well and Gavin gave her a lovely ride. I imagine we will try and step her up now. She looks like she will stay a mile and a half and we might try and go for a Listed race - Donnacha O'Brien, trainer.

going_detailed: Straight course - GOOD TO YIELDING changing to YIELDING after Race 1 (1.45); Round course - YIELDING

runners.name: Brewing
runners.comment: Six AW wins for William Haggas, 0-3 on turf, lacks a recent run, watch on stable debut
runners.spotlight: Formerly trained by William Haggas, for whom he amassed a record of 6-17, with all six wins coming on the AW; 0-3 on turf, his best effort coming on soft ground; lacks a recent outing and probably best watched on first run for new yard.

quotes.race: Try Unibet's New Acca Boosts Handicap
quotes.quote: It looked as though there'd be a good bit of pace on and it worked out that way. Going back up to 7f at a track he's won at before probably all helped but I think Brewing is a horse who is really learning how to drop into gear now, he's been winning but has still looking a bit immature about it but tonight he was direct and true. It was a good performance - Tom Marquand, jockey, speaking to Racing TV.

runners.name: Blues Emperor
runners.owner: Mrs H M Keaveney & Mark Keaveney

prev_owners.owner: Mrs H M Keaveney & M Keaveney

runners.comment: Won off 2lb lower at Fairyhouse in July, no impact since but has gone well here before
runners.spotlight: Won nicely at Fairyhouse (7f, good) in July off 89 and raised 7lb; hasn't figured in three starts since but mark has now slipped back to 91; went close on his only previous run over C&D; could bounce back.

quotes.race: Dubai Duty Free Derby Festival Handicap (Premier Handicap)
quotes.quote: Blues Emperor is very brave and when he gets his head in front he is hard to get past.

quotes.race: Tote Always SP Or Better Handicap
quotes.quote: Blues Emperor is a bonny little horse. We wondered would he handle this better ground but he is very tough and genuine. Hopefully he will make into a Premier Handicap horse - Johnny Murtagh, trainer.

Blues Emperor has probably done nothing but improve. He ran well at Dundalk and very well at Cork the last day. Ben (Coen) said he got into a pocket but he's very genuine, he tried his hardest when he got into the gap. We'll probably give him one more outing this season - Johnny Murtagh, trainer.

runners.name: I Am Superman

prev_owners.owner: M O'Callaghan Racing Limited, J Fleming & M O'Callaghan

runners.comment: 9yo, has run well in defeat this season in better races, big chance off a mark of 86
runners.spotlight: 9yo shaped well here in a valuable 7f handicap in June, beaten 2.75l into fifth off 89; followed that with another sound effort at the Curragh; below par the last twice but mark has now slipped to 86 and he's down in grade; big chance.

quotes.quote: I Am Superman hated the ground, just being a big strong horse he was able to get through it and get home. He is a very good horse on his day, and the end of last year I had the Buckingham Palace in my head. He is a Group horse and a straight seven at Ascot on fast ground where they go a lick will suit him - Michael O'Callaghan, trainer.

quotes.race: Family Fun Day August Bank Holiday Race
quotes.quote: It was a bit of a confidence booster for the horse and a bit of a relief for myself, because we know he has the ability - he has loads of talent - but at Ascot the whole occasion got to him and he raced too enthusiastically. He blew it by half way, whereas today they went a real good gallop and he travelled well. He did it very professionally. He raced a little bit in Leigh's hands early but he just needs to learn to race a little more - he's still learning. There's plenty more to come from him, he's just gone through the motions in what looked a good enough race on paper. After Ascot, today was about picking up the pieces and we'll figure out a plan from here - Michael O'Callaghan, trainer of I Am Superman

I Am Superman is a horse we always thought a lot of and he's making shapes of being a very nice horse. He made them look like handicappers. We might run him in the Tetrarch and if he came through that we can think about running in the Irish 2000 Guineas - Michael O'Callaghan, trainer.

I thought that was good performance carrying top weight and from that draw. He wasn't the quickest away but Leigh kept him out wide on the fresh ground down the back and at the apex of the bend was able to slot in in front and set his own fractions. He won well and he said he was just idling in front. I'm delighted with him and delighted that he's come good because we did think he was a nice horse last year. Hopefully he can progress well - Michael O'Callaghan, trainer

runners.name: Sujet
runners.comment: 2-2 on good ground this term, form of Killarney win boosted, big player
runners.spotlight: 3yo has won two of his three starts this season, his sole defeat coming his only start on soft ground; 1m1f Curragh premier handicap win on seasonal return off 11lb lower; beat recent emphatic Listowel winner Sunriseontheboyne in a rated race at Killarney on latest (1m, good); big player.

quotes.quote: Chris [Hayes] had Sujet in a lovely position throughout. When you are drawn wide here it is important to go and get a position otherwise you will be forced very wide over the nine furlongs, but he got him out and got him over. He tracked Ryan (Moore, on leader Mississippi Rover) and the plan was to have a go at him in the final furlong and that is just what he did. We'll see how he comes out of the race and another handicap will be the plan for him. He was gelded and just took a bit of time to come to himself. This was a lovely race for a three-year-old and he had been working nicely - Dermot Weld, trainer.

runners.name: Pier Pressure
runners.comment: Second 1m Gowran win on penultimate, sound Sovereign Path run latest, chance back at 1m
runners.spotlight: Gained his second career win and second win at Gowran off 4lb lower on penultimate (1m, good); ran on well for fifth off revised mark in the Sovereign Path (7f, good) latest; down 1lb and the return to 1m is a plus; considered.

quotes.race: Gateway Hotel Dundalk Race & Stay Maiden
quotes.quote: Pier Pressure travelled into it nicely, He was still green and had a good look when he got there but he won snug enough - Jack Kearney, rider

runners.name: Walhaan
runners.breeder: B Kennedy & Mrs Ann Marie Kennedy
runners.comment: Beaten a neck in this last year, 2lb lower now and claimer takes off 7lb, can't discount
runners.spotlight: Narrowly denied by Gerrit's Gem in this race last year off 86 and is 2lb lower now; two of last three runs have come over jumps; last turf run on the Flat a fine effort off 2lb higher at Leopardstown; can't be discounted with good claimer taking off 7lb.

quotes.quote: Walhaan got a no-nonsense ride, Eoin was very good on him. We felt he had improved since Navan and had this race pinpointed. The flat track and nice ground suited him well. He's really starting to get the hang of hurdling now - Ciaran Murphy, trainer.

stable_tour.quote: He won twice in France for Jean-Claude Rouget but has been winless since and has only just joined us after a season with Ian Williams, for whom he finished second twice at Ascot. They were good runs and fingers crossed we can do something with him this year off his mark of 90. From what he has shown me at home he could win off his mark. He may start off this week at Newcastle on Friday and I think as the season progresses he can win a race or two. 28-04-21

runners.name: Gerrits Gem
runners.comment: Last year's winner off 6lb lower, 3-3 at this venue inc' 6f win latest, go well again
runners.spotlight: Last year's winner off 74; three modest runs this season before rediscovering spark to win easily off 68 on return to this venue last time out (6f, soft); hiked up 12lb but is 3-3 at this venue and rider's 5lb claim a plus; go well again.

runners.name: Mathan
runners.comment: Second at Listowel last week, held by Sujet on Killarney running, best form on soft ground
runners.spotlight: Mostly running well in defeat this season; beaten 5l when second at Listowel (7f, heavy) a week ago; previously a 3.25l fifth behind Sujet in a rated race at Killarney and is worse off at weights here; would probably prefer softer ground.

quotes.quote: Mathan ran well the last day at the track and it looked like seven furlongs would suit him well on that occasion. Dylan kept it simple and he's a straightforward colt. It's nice to have a smart colt for Dean Reeves and Barry Fowler as they are two lovely people who have supported me well. I don't think it's unrealistic to think he could end up in stakes races and hopefully he can continue to progress. He's out of a Jeremy mare but he's not slow and his pedigree would give him a chance of getting a mile - Joseph O'Brien, trainer.

runners.name: Facethepuckout
runners.comment: Not that far behind Mathan when denied a clear run latest, 2lb below last win, chance
runners.spotlight: Second runner for yard; veteran shaped well behind Sun Soldier at Punchestown on his penultimate start; denied a clear run when not that far behind Mathan at Listowel last week; 2lb below last win and handles all ground; not dismissed.

quotes.quote: Facethepuckout has been consistent all year and been placed five times. That's his ground. The race just worked out for him as they have gone a real good gallop which he needs over seven. Leigh rode him for luck and it's worked out - Michael O'Callaghan, trainer

Facethepuckout came out of the Curragh race well. He's just sweet and in a good vein of form at the minute. He's well handicapped on his old form but chances are the handicapper will catch up with him - Michael O'Callaghan, trainer.
Facethepuckout was bought as a fun horse. He has sweetened up lovely and looked a different horse today. He's fit and well and went through the ground - Michael O'Callaghan, trainer.

quotes.race: Derek Ryan Live After Racing Nursery Handicap (Plus 10 Race)
quotes.quote: Donnacha [O'Brien] gave him a nice ride and on his Galway run he was entitled to be thereabouts. He'd probably be okay going a mile as well. He'll go for another nursery and I think there is more progression to come from him - Joseph O'Brien, trainer

runners.name: Solomon Coop
runners.comment: Has struggled since 13lb hike for 1m2f Fairyhouse win, may be on a tough mark
runners.spotlight: Scored at Fairyhouse (1m2f, yielding) in May off 66; handicapper took a dim view and raised him 13lb; has struggled off his revised mark in three starts since and assessor slow to relent; may be on a tough mark.

runners.name: Sun Soldier
runners.owner: A Oliver & Blue Candi Lab London Limited
runners.comment: Up 7lb for 1m Punchestown win on latest, blinkers retained, should go well again
runners.spotlight: 3yo gained breakthrough success in first-time blinkers (retained) at Punchestown (1m, gd-yld) on latest (Facethepuckout fourth); 7lb rise seems fair enough and he should go well again.

runners.name: Jamarr
runners.comment: Two-time AW winner, 0-9 on turf, poor in handicaps the last twice, others appeal more
runners.spotlight: 3yo won two on the AW last season; 0-9 on turf, though he did go close in a 6.5f Limerick rated race in July; no show in two handicaps since that run and was slowly away last time at the Curragh; others appeal more.

runners.name: Zaraahmando
runners.comment: Up 7lb for third win of season over C&D latest, career best needed in deeper race
runners.spotlight: Won his third race of the season over C&D earlier this month on soft ground; raised 7lb for that 0.5l success; better ground is fine for this 3yo but he'll need a big career best to follow up in this much deeper race.

runners.name: Falls Of Acharn
runners.comment: Won Leopardstown maiden latest, form has been knocked, tough ask in first handicap
runners.spotlight: 3yo got off the mark at the third attempt in a Leopardstown maiden last month (1m, good); runner up let the form down since and this is a hot race in which to make his handicap debut; respected but others preferred.

going_detailed: Straight course - GOOD TO YIELDING changing to YIELDING after Race 1 (1.45); Round course - YIELDING

runners.name: Vierson
runners.comment: AW maiden winner in January; turf peaks are respected; soft ground an excuse last time
runners.spotlight: AW maiden winner in January; second in 1m2f handicap at Roscommon in May and third at the Curragh in July (1m); soft ground perhaps no help last time; possibilities.

runners.name: Mapa
runners.comment: Eleven-race maiden; hasn't offered much in handicaps and a tongue-tie is tried
runners.spotlight: Best runs have been in maidens, though not last time tried at 1m4f; hasn't offered much in handicaps and a tongue-tie is tried.

runners.name: Venetian
runners.comment: Three wins in Britain at about 1m and nearly won again at Dundalk four days ago
runners.spotlight: Three wins in Britain at about 1m and nearly won again at Dundalk four days ago when collared late on by Famous Enough; fine on turf and should have every chance.

runners.name: Famous Enough
runners.comment: Not weighted to confirm last Friday's AW placings with Venetian
runners.spotlight: Course winner who doubled his tally when running on well to thwart Venetian on the AW last Friday (1m); no good thing to confirm those placings as he's essentially 11lb higher, carrying a penalty and rated 4lb lower on the AW.

runners.name: Purring Along
runners.comment: Back to a better mark and respectable fourth of 15 last time at Gowran
runners.spotlight: Four-time winner and only 2lb higher than for her Down Royal win in June (7f, good); respectable fourth of 15 last time at Gowran (1m, heavy).

quotes.quote: PURRING ALONG was working the best she's ever worked the past week. We brought her up to the beach the other day and I don't think I've ever seen a horse so fresh so it was a good omen coming into today. She got a little nick one day out in the paddock so she hasn't ran in a few weeks. Easy ground and a good pace suits - Shane Duffy, trainer.

runners.name: Una Matata
runners.comment: Won a 7f turf maiden last year but has been below that form since and needs a revival
runners.spotlight: Won a 7f turf maiden last year but has been below that form since and needs a revival.

runners.name: Relevant Range
runners.comment: Hard to predict but 2lb lower than for last September's win (1m, good)
runners.spotlight: Testing ground an excuse last week at Listowel and that was after a lengthy break; hard to predict but 2lb lower than for last September's win (1m, good).

quotes.quote: Relevant Range was flat out the whole way but Darragh got him travelling and enthusiastic. It was a fantastic ride because the hors isn't the most genuine - Gillian Scott, trainer.

runners.name: Sayfa Fad
runners.comment: Won last turf race (7lb lower) and a wide draw made life difficult on the AW last time
runners.spotlight: Came from well back to collect over 1m at Bellewstown (good to yielding); 7lb higher now but a wide draw made life difficult at Dundalk last time.

runners.name: Super Over

prev_owners.owner: Ciaran J Mooney/Mark McCloskey/Adam Mooney/Colm Holmes

runners.comment: Regressive in the last year and was poor on debut for this yard last time
runners.spotlight: Four AW wins up to 1m; regressive in the last year and was poor on debut for this yard last time; not easy to fancy.

quotes.quote: Super Over is very consistent and he loves this place. He was good and gutsy. He's a jockey's dream ride. He wings the gates, he relaxes and he is very straightforward - Colin Keane, rider

quotes.race: Story Of Dundalk Stadium Book Buy Online Apprentice Rated Race
quotes.quote: Maybe 7f was a little short for Super Over the last day but I thought he'd stay 1m well and I was happy to get a lead. I arrived there well and he stayed at it - Sam Ewing, jockey, talking to Racing TV.

runners.name: La Tulipe Noire

prev_owners.owner: Mrs Magette Meagher & Thomas P Meagher

runners.comment: 1-32; hasn't been running badly but she's opposable for win purposes
runners.spotlight: Only 1-32 and that success came on the AW; hasn't been running badly but she's opposable for win purposes.

quotes.quote: La Tulipe Noire jumped okay, there wasn't much pace on and I was able to dictate. The blinkers helped her. She was tough and always doing enough, Declan McDonogh, rider.

runners.name: Liamo
runners.comment: Had a good year and continues to run well, but current mark looks troublesome
runners.spotlight: Has continued to run well since his Listowel win in June (7f, good), including back there last week (heavy); however, this mark (8lb above that last win) is looking troublesome.

quotes.quote: Liamo liked the ground and I'd say that is the way to ride him, just hold onto him and come with one run. We are getting to know him now. He got a bit upset at the start when we were adjusting his girth. The owners are local. They are from Dunguib so it is nice to win in their back garden. They are two brothers and their sons would be riding only for he is too low in the weight. I had a few two-year-olds before but they didn't work out so it is nice to get the first one - Brendan Walsh, trainer.

runners.name: Micasso
runners.comment: Never involved last week at Listowel but probably wants this drier ground
runners.spotlight: Nine-race maiden who never got involved from off the pace last week at Listowel (7f, heavy); probably wants this drier ground and worth another go at 1m.

runners.name: My Girl Robyn
runners.comment: 50-1 for last Friday's handicap debut at Dundalk and was well behind two of these
runners.spotlight: 50-1 for last Friday's handicap debut at Dundalk and was well behind two of these.

runners.name: Tynamite
runners.comment: Six AW wins but is 0-31 on turf and has to put three below par runs behind him
runners.spotlight: Six AW wins but is 0-31 on turf and has to put three below par runs behind him.

quotes.race: Irish Racing Fundraiser for Children's Health Foundation Crumlin In Memory Of Pat Smullen Handicap
quotes.quote: Tynamite did it well in the end. The step back in trip suited him and he just needs a bit of tricking for to go. Coming between horses helps him - Oisin Orr, rider

quotes.race: LMFM Dual Race Night Friday 3rd May Handicap
quotes.quote: Tynamite was running over his trip today. He needs things to fall right. He got a brilliant ride tonight and he has the ability to win again - David Marnane, trainer.

He was always showing a bit of nice work at home but he didn't like soft ground. Both times he's run here he's respectably. We may try and run him next Friday night as long as the handicapper doesn't kill us - Paul McEnery, trainer

runners.name: Swiss Army Officer
runners.comment: Infrequent winner not in the best of form and he's 8lb out of the weights
runners.spotlight: Infrequent winner not in the best of form and he's 8lb out of the weights.

quotes.quote: Swiss Army Officer was running in big fields at Leopardstown all season and was never beaten far. He needs his own way and he got it. Emmet kidded him along and he won well in the end. These races are probably ideal for him - Kevin Coleman, trainer.
